               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18361128-224-charge-1" targOrder="Y" targets="def1-224-18361128 t18361128-224-offence-1 t18361128-224-verdict-1"></join>
               <p>224. <persName id="def1-224-18361128" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-224-18361128" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-224-18361128" type="age" value="23"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-224-18361128" type="surname" value="CRISP"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-224-18361128" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">EDWARD CRISP</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18361128-224-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18361128-224-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="deception"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18361128-224-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="fraud"></interp> for a misdemeanor.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361128-name-1513" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1513" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1513" type="surname" value="LIFELY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1513" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS LIFELY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a horse-keeper, and live at Battersea, Surrey. I be<lb></lb>long to a club, of which John Mayhew is a member—we have a fund among ourselves to give relief to the members in sickness—I act as treasurer to pay the money—on the 6th of November the prisoner came to me on the subject of a person of the name of John Mayhew, to whom there was a sum of 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. due considering him as a member of the club—when the prisoner came he said that John Mayhew was very bad, his wife could not leave him to come, and had asked him (the prisoner) to come—he said he came for John Mayhew's sick money—I paid him 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361128-name-1514" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1514" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1514" type="surname" value="MAYHEW"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1514" type="given" value="ELLEN"></interp>ELLEN MAYHEW</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in the parish of Wandsworth, Surrey—my hus<lb></lb>band was sick—I gave no direction to the prisoner to go Lifely on the 6th of November—I had on a former occasion, on the 23rd of October, to get the money due to my husband—he got 6<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. on the 26th, and brought it me home—he told me he had put it on the chimney-piece—I was not at home at the time—he told me of it, and found we had got 6<hi rend="italic">s</hi>—I did not send him the second time.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361128-name-1515" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1515" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1515" type="surname" value="LIFELY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1515" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS LIFELY</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> On the 26th of October I paid the pri<lb></lb>soner 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., and 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. on the 6th of November.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361128-name-1516" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1516" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1516" type="surname" value="MAYHEW"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1516" type="given" value="ELLEN"></interp>ELLEN MAYHEW</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> The prisoner did not bring any money to me or my husband on the 6th of November, nor had I sent him for it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> The first time you sent me was on Sunday morning—Tho<lb></lb>mas Lifely said he must see his master, and I went on Monday—he did not pay—on Tuesday he gave me 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—I brought you 6<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., and you asked me to go on the 6th of November. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> No, I did not.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361128-name-1517" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1517" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1517" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1517" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH SMITH</persName>
                  </hi>. I saw Lifely pay the prisoner 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. on the 26th of Oc<lb></lb>tober, in Wandsworth parish, on the Tooting road.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361128-name-1518" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1518" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1518" type="surname" value="CLARK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1518" type="given" value="TERENCE"></interp>TERENCE CLARK</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable V</hi> 107.) I apprehended the prisoner in Wandsworth.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> The women asked me to go on the 6th of November in the own house—I do not know that there was any body there.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361128-name-1519" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1519" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1519" type="surname" value="MAYHEW"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1519" type="given" value="ELLEN"></interp>ELLEN MAYHEW</persName>
                  </hi>. I undertake to swear that I never authorized him to get money except on the 26th of October.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">JURY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Was he in the habit of coming backwards and forwards to see you husband? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—from their being brought up together in the same place—I cannot tell whether he was there on the 4th, 5th, or 6th of November, but I did not give him authority to receive this.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Did you not go with me afterwards to see what was allowed? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes; I did not send you three times before I went with you—I</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183611280241"></xptr>
               <p>did not know when I was to have any more, and I went with you to the place where I was to get it, but I did not see Mr. Lifely.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">JURY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did the prisoner take you there? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, all along the railroad—he did not take me to any house—he went down to the stable—I did not go there—that was about a fortnight after I had the 6<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—he went to the stable, and said the man was not there—I was going to hear what was due, and to get it myself—he never gave me the 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>—the sum allowed was 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. a week.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361128-name-1520" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1520" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1520" type="surname" value="LIFELY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1520" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS LIFELY</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined. Q.</hi> Did he apply to you after the 6th of November? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, once more—I never saw the woman—I let him have 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. after the 6th of November.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">
                     <rs id="t18361128-224-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
